
[1]insecurity

   INSECU'RITY, n. [in and security.] Want of safety, or want of
   confidence in safety. Seamen in a tempest must be conscious of their
   insecurity.

   1. Uncertainty. With what insecurity of truth we ascribe effects or
   unseen causes.

   2. Want of safety; danger; hazard; exposure to destruction or loss;
   applied to things; as the insecurity of a building exposed to fire; the
   insecurity of a debt.
